{{Infobox font | name = Tratex | image = Tratex_font_sample.png | style = [[Sans-serif]] | classifications = [[sans-serif|Geometric sans-serif]] | prop = Proportional | date = 2002 | creator = Karl-Gustav Gustafson | foundry = Vägverket | sample = [[Image:Tratex Svart.svg|240px]] | based_on = [[Highway Gothic|FHWA]] |}}
'''Tratex''' (earlier called GePos) is a [[geometric sans-serif]] [[typeface]] family for [[road signs in Sweden]]. It was developed for maximal readability in traffic, and designed by [[Kåge Gustafsson|Karl-Gustaf Gustafsson]] (known as Kåge Gustafsson).<ref>[[Göteborgs-Posten|GP]]: ''[http://www.gp.se/motor/1.851645-i-djungeln-av-vagvisare I djungeln av vägvisare] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121012003044/http://www.gp.se/motor/1.851645-i-djungeln-av-vagvisare |date=2012-10-12 }}'' {{sv icon}}, read May 30, 2013.</ref>
Tratex also contains [[Sami languages|Sami]] characters. It is free to download and use for illustrations and prints.
